        "name": "secure-code-review",
        "description": "Use when reviewing or writing code that handles user input, authentication, or file I/O.",
        "content": "## Secure Code Review Checklist\n\n**Input Validation:** Never trust user-supplied input; validate type, length, and format at boundaries.\n\n**Secrets:** No hardcoded passwords or API keys. Use environment variables.\n\n**Auth:** Verify authorization on every protected endpoint, not just at login."
      },
      {
        "name": "golang-best-practices",
        "description": "Use when writing or reviewing Go code.",
        "content": "## Go Best Practices\n\n- Use `context.Context` for cancellation and timeouts on all external calls.\n- Return errors rather than panicking in library code.\n- Use `errgroup` for concurrent operations with shared cancellation.\n- Keep error wrapping with `fmt.Errorf(\"doing X: %w\", err)`.\n- Avoid mutexes if channels and goroutines suffice.\n- Use `sync.Pool` for frequently allocated objects."
      }
    ],
