        "name": "precision-on-numbers",
        "description": "Use when the user asks about financial data, market prices, or quantitative comparisons.",
        "content": "## Precision on Numbers\n\nWhen citing specific financial or numerical data:\n- Clearly label whether figures are estimates or exact.\n- State the currency, units, and time period.\n- Note the source and when it was retrieved.\n- Flag if data may be stale or estimated."
      }
